                                <h1 class="cpp-h1">Scholarships</h1>





                                    <section class="text-images" id="s0">










                                            <p align="center">\xc2\xa0</p>
<p>The below scholarships are available to the Civil Enigneering and Construction Engineering and Management students. The requirements, eligibility, and deadline for application of each of the scholarships might be different, which can be found below.\xc2\xa0</p>
<p>Please visit the following webpage for submiting your application:\xc2\xa0 \xc2\xa0 \xc2\xa0 <a href="https://csupomona.academicworks.com/">https://csupomona.academicworks.com/</a></p>
            </section>

























                       <section aria-labelledby="qa-h2-2" class="mt-4">
        <h2 id="qa-h2-2">Applications</h2>
                        <div class="accordion" id="accordion-2">



                        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header" id="heading1">
                <h3 class="m-0">
                    <button aria-controls="collapse2-1" aria-expanded="false" class="btn btn-link" data-target="#collapse2-1" data-toggle="collapse">









                                                  Eng - CE - Civil Engineering Department Outstanding Student Scholarship
                    </button>
                </h3>
            </div>
                            <div aria-labelledby="heading1" class="collapse " data-parent="#accordion-2" id="collapse2-1">
                          <div class="card-body">










                                                The Civil Engineering Department Outstanding Student Scholarship is available to all continuing CE students that hold a full-time status. Financial need is not considered. The purpose of this scholarship is to recognize students that have excellent academic records, and outstanding work ethic, while being active in extracurricular activities.

              </div>
            </div>
        </div>


                    </div>   
            </section>













                                       <div class="accordion" id="accordion-3">



                        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header" id="heading1">
                <h2 class="m-0">
                    <button aria-controls="collapse3-1" aria-expanded="false" class="btn btn-link" data-target="#collapse3-1" data-toggle="collapse">









                                                  Engineering - CE - Geomatics Engineering Scholarship by Wood Rogers Inc.
                    </button>
                </h2>
            </div>
                            <div aria-labelledby="heading1" class="collapse " data-parent="#accordion-3" id="collapse3-1">
                          <div class="card-body">










                                                <p>The Geomatics Engineering Scholarship by Wood Rogers Inc. was created and funded by Wood Rogers Inc. to promote the interest in the geospatial and land surveying profession. Cal Poly Pomona Civil Engineering department will select two students for this scholarship. Each will receive $1,000 to help cover college fees and living expenses.<br/><br/></p>
<p><br/>*Selection Criteria:*<br/> * Open to all class level: Freshman, Sophomore, Junior, Senior and Graduates (including first-freshman and transfer) <br/> * Major must be Civil Engineering major with declared Geospatial Engineering option<br/> * Must be enrolled full-time (12 or more units) during the entire awarding period<br/> * Must have a minimum cumulative GPA of 3.0 or higher<br/><br/>*Funds Available:*<br/> * One scholarship in the amount of $1,000 for incoming freshmen or transfer student<br/> * One scholarship in the amount of $1,000 for a continuing student<br/><br/>Selected applications will be auto-matched based on their completed general application. Eligible winner(s) will be notified via email.</p>

              </div>
            </div>
        </div>


                    </div>   













                                       <div class="accordion" id="accordion-4">



                        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header" id="heading1">
                <h2 class="m-0">
                    <button aria-controls="collapse4-1" aria-expanded="false" class="btn btn-link" data-target="#collapse4-1" data-toggle="collapse">









                                                  Engineering - CE - Huff Family Scholarship
                    </button>
                </h2>
            </div>
                            <div aria-labelledby="heading1" class="collapse " data-parent="#accordion-4" id="collapse4-1">
                          <div class="card-body">










                                                This scholarship is open to continuing freshman in the College of Engineering whose demonstrate an interest in civil engineering. <br/><br/><br/>*Selection Criteria:*<br/> * Open to class levels Freshman Only <br/> * Major must be Civil Engineering <br/> * Must have a minimum cumulative GPA of 3.0 or higher<br/> * Submit a copy of your unofficial transcript with your Fall grades<br/> * Demonstrate financial need by completing the FAFSA for 2020-2021<br/> * Submit a 500-word essay detailing your financial need and your motivation to become a civil engineer<br/> * Must be enrolled full-time (12 or more units) during the awarding academic year<br/> * California residency is required<br/><br/><br/>Award winners will be determined based on their academic ability, motivation, and financial need.

              </div>
            </div>
        </div>


                    </div>   













                                       <div class="accordion" id="accordion-5">



                        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header" id="heading1">
                <h2 class="m-0">
                    <button aria-controls="collapse5-1" aria-expanded="false" class="btn btn-link" data-target="#collapse5-1" data-toggle="collapse">









                                                  Engineering - CE - James Gates Scholarship Endowment
                    </button>
                </h2>
            </div>
                            <div aria-labelledby="heading1" class="collapse " data-parent="#accordion-5" id="collapse5-1">
                          <div class="card-body">










                                                <p>This scholarship is offering awards to undergraduate students whose a Civil Engineering major and have completed at least 30 or more CE program units. <br/><br/>*Selection Criteria:*<br/> * Open to all class level: Freshman, Sophomore, Junior and Senior<br/> * Student must be first generation<br/> * Must be major in Civil Engineering <br/> * Must have a minimum major and cumulative GPA of 3.0 or higher<br/> * Demonstrate financial need by completing the FAFSA for 2020-2021<br/> * Submit a one-page essay describing your entrepreneurial activities, experiences or plans in civil engineering<br/> * Must be enrolled full-time (12 or more units) for the fall and spring semester of 2020-2021 AY <br/> * California residency required.\xc2\xa0</p>
<p><br/>Selection will be based on students' entrepreneurial POTENTIAL, essay, and financial need.\xc2\xa0<br/><br/></p>

              </div>
