                </h2>
            </div>
                            <div aria-labelledby="heading1" class="collapse " data-parent="#accordion-8" id="collapse8-1">
                          <div class="card-body">










                                                This scholarship program was started by Melissa Demirci who is an alumna of Cal Poly Pomona\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s College of Engineering from the Civil Engineering Program who also supports the Women in Engineering program. Her parents founded Transtech Engineers, Inc. in 1989 and since graduating from Cal Poly Pomona, Melissa Demirci has taken an active role in the firm\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s leadership and wanted to use this platform to give back to the students within the Civil Engineering Program through the Transtech Engineers Scholarship Fund. <br/><br/>*Selection criteria to award:<br/> * Opened to continuing junior and senior students majoring in Civil Engineering <br/> * Must have cumulative GPA of 3.0 or higher<br/> * Must be enrolled full-time <br/> * Student must complete the supplemental question(s)<br/> * Student must submit 1 Letter of Recommendation<br/><br/>Awards each year are based on the student\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s general application and supplemental responses, consisting of academic and co-curricular excellence, and essay content. <br/><br/>Should you have any questions, please contact Norma De La Llata at nedelallata@cpp.edu, in the College of Engineering.

