                </h2>
            </div>
                            <div aria-labelledby="heading1" class="collapse " data-parent="#accordion-12" id="collapse12-1">
                          <div class="card-body">










                                                <p>Donald G. Wells was a Civil engineering professor and a leader in the environmental and water resources group within the Civil Engineering Department. This scholarship was established to provide support and reward those who have some involvement in their profession using engineering skills/knowledge in some way beyond taking classes. <br/>This scholarship is renewable (dependent on available funds) for the awarding recipient who continues to meet the criteria.<br/><br/><br/>*Selection Criteria:<br/> * Open to current grade level: Junior and Senior including first-time transfers <br/> * Major must be in Civil Engineering<br/> * Must have worked or intern in the field of civil engineering or participated in networking with the industry/employers. <br/> * Must maintain a minimum of 3.0 GPA or higher<br/> * Answer the supplemental question(s) <br/><br/><br/>For more information on this scholarship opportunity, please visit this website at https://givingday.cpp.edu/campaigns/donald-g-wells-memorial-scholarship</p>

